00:06:06,640 --> 00:06:08,820
when it interacts with the spin,

154
00:06:09,020 --> 00:06:11,220
it produces a number in the window,

155
00:06:11,900 --> 00:06:13,780
and that number in the window

156
00:06:13,780 --> 00:06:15,660
is either plus one or minus one.

157
00:06:15,880 --> 00:06:18,980
No matter what direction the apparatus is pointing in,

158
00:06:19,020 --> 00:06:21,060
and no matter what has happened to the spin beforehand.

159
00:06:21,060 --> 00:06:24,320
When the apparatus is pointing up,

160
00:06:24,960 --> 00:06:28,260
we will say that what it has

161
00:06:28,260 --> 00:06:31,560
measured is the z component of spin.

162
00:06:31,840 --> 00:06:33,460
Let's put some axes in here.

163
00:06:33,700 --> 00:06:34,860
Z up,

164
00:06:34,860 --> 00:06:36,520
x to the right,

165
00:06:36,520 --> 00:06:38,380
and y out of the blackboard.

166
00:06:39,300 --> 00:06:41,460
And when the apparatus is pointing up,

167
00:06:41,640 --> 00:06:46,260
we'll say that it produces an experimental number

168
00:06:46,920 --> 00:06:49,240
which measures the z component of the spin.

169
00:06:51,060 --> 00:06:52,990
Now is that particularly interesting to

170
00:06:52,990 --> 00:06:54,920
