300
00:11:32,180 --> 00:11:33,670
there is no way that it

301
00:11:33,670 --> 00:11:35,160
would just give plus or minus one.

302
00:11:36,680 --> 00:11:37,760
Components of vectors,

303
00:11:37,760 --> 00:11:39,550
even if the vector is

304
00:11:39,550 --> 00:11:41,340
required to have exactly unit length,

305
00:11:41,480 --> 00:11:43,380
here's a vector with exactly unit length,

306
00:11:43,480 --> 00:11:45,660
a pointer,

307
00:11:45,660 --> 00:11:46,420
a three vector,

308
00:11:46,420 --> 00:11:47,520
a vector of exactly unit length.

309
00:11:48,300 --> 00:11:50,620
If we turn it and do other things with it,

310
00:11:50,700 --> 00:11:53,390
the x component or the z component can

311
00:11:53,390 --> 00:11:56,080
be any number between minus one and one.

312
00:11:56,640 --> 00:11:58,140
So this is a funny vector

313
00:11:58,140 --> 00:11:59,640
if it's a vector at all.

314
00:12:01,640 --> 00:12:02,800
But still it does seem

315
00:12:02,800 --> 00:12:03,960
