338
00:12:52,920 --> 00:12:56,300
So something's funny,

339
00:12:56,440 --> 00:12:59,580
but what is true is that the

340
00:12:59,580 --> 00:13:02,720
average value of sigma x will be one,

341
00:13:02,900 --> 00:13:03,300
sorry,

342
00:13:03,300 --> 00:13:06,680
will be zero if the initial starting point was

343
00:13:06,680 --> 00:13:10,060
a spin that was up along the z axis.

344
00:13:11,180 --> 00:13:12,980
Same for the y axis.

345
00:13:12,980 --> 00:13:15,490
If the initial value of the spin was

346
00:13:15,490 --> 00:13:18,000
prepared to be up along the z axis,

347
00:13:18,340 --> 00:13:23,000
and you rotate the apparatus into the y orientation,

348
00:13:23,720 --> 00:13:24,320
again,

349
00:13:24,320 --> 00:13:25,680
you'll have equal probability.

350
00:13:26,520 --> 00:13:28,150
And so the average value

351
00:13:28,150 --> 00:13:29,780
of sigma y will be zero.

352
00:13:30,580 --> 00:13:32,300
You can even go beyond that.

353
00:13:32,580 --> 00:13:33,160
You can say,

354
00:13:33,160 --> 00:13:35,060
let's start with the apparatus,

355
00:13:35,300 --> 00:13:36,120
not vertical,

356
00:13:36,320 --> 00:13:39,980
but let's start with the apparatus along the x direction.

357
00:13:41,180 --> 00:13:42,960
Use it to prepare the spin.

358
00:13:42,980 --> 00:13:45,340
So that it's known to be

359
00:13:45,340 --> 00:13:47,700
pointing horizontal along the x direction,

360
00:13:47,960 --> 00:13:48,360
in other words,

361
00:13:48,360 --> 00:13:49,920
sigma x is equal to plus one,

362
00:13:50,460 --> 00:13:52,440
and then do a y or z experiment.

363
00:13:54,000 --> 00:13:54,480
Always,

364
00:13:54,480 --> 00:13:56,630
we will get random but

365
00:13:56,630 --> 00:13:58,780
equal probabilities for up and down.

366
00:13:59,540 --> 00:14:01,280
Or plus and minus one.

367
00:14:03,280 --> 00:14:04,460
You go a little bit further.

368
00:14:09,120 --> 00:14:09,940
Now of course,

369
00:14:09,940 --> 00:14:12,400
I am quoting what would be the results

370
00:14:12,400 --> 00:14:14,600
of experiments on spins.

371
00:14:15,420 --> 00:14:17,100
I've never done such an experiment.

372
00:14:17,260 --> 00:14:18,080
I don't think I could.

373
00:14:19,520 --> 00:14:21,470
But I have no doubt that if

374
00:14:21,470 --> 00:14:23,420
I had the skill to do it,

375
00:14:23,440 --> 00:14:24,200
this is what would happen.

376
00:14:25,760 --> 00:14:26,160
What?

377
00:14:26,900 --> 00:14:28,810
Suppose we start out and we

378
00:14:28,810 --> 00:14:30,720
have not prepared the spin at all.

379
00:14:30,780 --> 00:14:31,140
Doesn't matter.

380
00:14:31,540 --> 00:14:31,940
Okay,

381
00:14:31,940 --> 00:14:32,220
go ahead.

382
00:14:32,540 --> 00:14:34,990
So it could be up or

383
00:14:34,990 --> 00:14:37,440
down or x or y or z.

384
00:14:37,500 --> 00:14:39,260
We don't know what it's past.

385
00:14:39,300 --> 00:14:40,000
We don't know what it is.

386
00:14:40,040 --> 00:14:40,240
Right.

387
00:14:40,240 --> 00:14:42,910
And we set it up so that the

388
00:14:42,910 --> 00:14:45,580
apparatus is on its side along the x axis.

389
00:14:45,740 --> 00:14:45,900
Okay.

390
00:14:48,100 --> 00:14:49,840
And we do lots of measurements.

391
00:14:50,700 --> 00:14:51,340
What's going on?

392
00:14:51,500 --> 00:14:51,580
Well,

393
00:14:51,580 --> 00:14:53,840
we first do one measurement before we do anything else.

394
00:14:54,700 --> 00:14:55,060
Yeah,

395
00:14:55,060 --> 00:14:56,320
let me come back for a second.

396
00:14:56,500 --> 00:14:57,460
Let me come back a second.

397
00:14:57,640 --> 00:14:57,760
Okay.

398
00:14:59,120 --> 00:14:59,680
You're right.

399
00:14:59,740 --> 00:15:01,430
We want to do a lot of experiments

400
00:15:01,430 --> 00:15:03,120
and a lot of measurements and quantum mechanics.

401
00:15:03,480 --> 00:15:04,690
There are two distinct ways

402
00:15:04,690 --> 00:15:05,900
we could do lots of experiments.

403
00:15:06,160 --> 00:15:07,060
It really doesn't matter which,

404
00:15:07,060 --> 00:15:07,920
which we do.

405
00:15:08,520 --> 00:15:10,220
We could imagine having a log of,

406
00:15:10,240 --> 00:15:12,940
a large number of identical spins prepared at the beginning,

407
00:15:13,140 --> 00:15:14,420
however they were prepared.

408
00:15:15,320 --> 00:15:17,060
And we can do experiments

409
00:15:17,060 --> 00:15:18,800
on a large number of them.

410
00:15:20,100 --> 00:15:23,880
Or we can do repeated experiments on the same spin.

411
00:15:25,540 --> 00:15:26,860
To a large extent it

412
00:15:26,860 --> 00:15:28,180
doesn't matter which we're talking about.

413
00:15:28,360 --> 00:15:29,600
And I'll tell you when it matters.

414
00:15:30,080 --> 00:15:31,290
But at the moment all

415
00:15:31,290 --> 00:15:32,500
we're talking about is one spin.

416
00:15:33,560 --> 00:15:37,100
You said start the apparatus horizontal,

417
00:15:37,920 --> 00:15:39,340
stick the spin into it,

418
00:15:39,340 --> 00:15:41,080
and detect what you get.

419
00:15:42,000 --> 00:15:43,090
What you get will either

420
00:15:43,090 --> 00:15:44,180
be plus one or minus one.

421
00:15:44,840 --> 00:15:45,200
Okay?

422
00:15:47,180 --> 00:15:48,960
You could then take the spin out of there.

423
00:15:50,300 --> 00:15:51,830
Give it to your friend

424
00:15:51,830 --> 00:15:53,360
who does some magic with spins.

425
00:15:53,520 --> 00:15:54,440
You don't know what it is.

426
00:15:54,520 --> 00:15:56,360
You don't know what the hell he does with it.

427
00:15:56,960 --> 00:15:57,960
He flips it around,

428
00:15:57,960 --> 00:15:58,800
juggles it,

429
00:15:58,880 --> 00:15:59,960
puts it in his pocket,

430
00:15:59,960 --> 00:16:00,560
takes it out,

431
00:16:00,560 --> 00:16:01,400
and gives it back to you,

432
00:16:01,480 --> 00:16:02,940
and tells you to do it again.

433
00:16:03,699 --> 00:16:04,060
Again,

434
00:16:04,060 --> 00:16:05,880
you'll get plus one or minus one.

435
00:16:06,660 --> 00:16:08,360
It may be that he did nothing,

436
00:16:08,360 --> 00:16:10,250
in which case the second time you'll get

437
00:16:10,250 --> 00:16:12,140
the same answer you got the first time.

438
00:16:13,280 --> 00:16:15,280
Or it may have been that he turned it over,

439
00:16:15,380 --> 00:16:16,960
in which case you'll get the opposite answer.

440
00:16:17,100 --> 00:16:17,920
But whatever you get,

441
00:16:17,920 --> 00:16:19,380
it will be plus one or minus one.

442
00:16:20,380 --> 00:16:20,800
Okay.

443
00:16:21,760 --> 00:16:24,800
Then if you do a repeated experiment

444
00:16:25,360 --> 00:16:26,770
knowing that nothing else was

445
00:16:26,770 --> 00:16:28,180
done to the spin in between,

446
00:16:28,800 --> 00:16:29,940
you'll get the same answer

447
00:16:29,940 --> 00:16:31,080
if you do the same experiment.

448
00:16:31,520 --> 00:16:31,940
Okay?

449
00:16:33,160 --> 00:16:33,580
That's,

450
00:16:33,580 --> 00:16:33,940
uh...

451
00:16:35,780 --> 00:16:36,200
Good.

452
00:16:36,540 --> 00:16:36,960
Okay,

453
00:16:36,960 --> 00:16:38,160
so let's be a little more general.

454
00:16:38,900 --> 00:16:41,740
Let's suppose that we orient the

455
00:16:41,740 --> 00:16:44,580
axis of the detector in any direction.

456
00:16:44,960 --> 00:16:47,360
So let's make a notation for a direction.

457
00:16:47,580 --> 00:16:49,580
A unit three vector.

458
00:16:49,980 --> 00:16:51,700
A unit three vector...

459
00:16:53,100 --> 00:16:55,440
Unit vectors in three-dimensional space

460
00:16:55,440 --> 00:16:57,820
are always indicated by putting a

461
00:16:57,820 --> 00:17:00,200
little hat on top of the symbol.

462
00:17:01,140 --> 00:17:04,520
So this is a unit vector along a particular axis.

463
00:17:05,260 --> 00:17:06,980
We start with our detector

464
00:17:06,980 --> 00:17:08,900
along the axis M,

465
00:17:09,980 --> 00:17:11,859
not horizontal,

466
00:17:11,859 --> 00:17:12,819
not vertical,

467
00:17:12,819 --> 00:17:13,780
not in or out,

468
00:17:13,980 --> 00:17:18,480
but just catty-cornered in some...

469
00:17:23,689 --> 00:17:25,079
some complicated way.

470
00:17:25,280 --> 00:17:26,240
There's M.

471
00:17:29,820 --> 00:17:30,880
There's M.

472
00:17:31,580 --> 00:17:32,440
And...

473
00:17:34,260 --> 00:17:35,120
uh...

474
00:17:35,120 --> 00:17:36,860
We start with the spin.

475
00:17:37,020 --> 00:17:38,540
Let's start with the spin

476
00:17:39,120 --> 00:17:42,640
previously having been oriented or prepared

477
00:17:42,640 --> 00:17:44,840
along a different axis,

478
00:17:45,180 --> 00:17:46,720
the N axis.

479
00:17:47,580 --> 00:17:48,860
How do we do that?

480
00:17:49,080 --> 00:17:49,440
Well,

481
00:17:49,440 --> 00:17:52,000
I should have gone a little slower.

482
00:17:52,420 --> 00:17:56,120
We start with the detector along the N axis.

483
00:17:56,720 --> 00:18:00,780
Do an experiment and discover that along the N axis

484
00:18:00,780 --> 00:18:03,720
the spin comes up plus one.

485
00:18:04,360 --> 00:18:08,620
Then we rotate the apparatus into the M direction,

486
00:18:10,000 --> 00:18:12,700
and we do another experiment on the same spin.

487
00:18:13,420 --> 00:18:15,690
It will either come up plus one

488
00:18:15,690 --> 00:18:17,960
or minus one along the M axis,

489
00:18:18,300 --> 00:18:19,660
never in between,

490
00:18:21,160 --> 00:18:23,880
but the average value of the

491
00:18:23,880 --> 00:18:26,600
spin along the M axis here

492
00:18:27,440 --> 00:18:28,840
will not be one.

493
00:18:28,980 --> 00:18:30,400
It will not be minus one.

494
00:18:30,400 --> 00:18:31,600
What will it be?

495
00:18:31,900 --> 00:18:33,820
It will be the cosine of

496
00:18:33,820 --> 00:18:35,740
