497
00:18:36,120 --> 00:18:37,100
In other words,

498
00:18:37,100 --> 00:18:41,220
the component of M along N.

499
00:18:42,100 --> 00:18:43,200
How do we write that?

500
00:18:43,280 --> 00:18:43,840
Let's write that.

501
00:18:44,680 --> 00:18:46,140
Let's write a formula for that.

502
00:18:47,200 --> 00:18:49,820
The symbol for averages in quantum mechanics

503
00:18:50,180 --> 00:18:52,940
are a pair of angular brackets like this.

504
00:18:53,780 --> 00:18:55,080
This one is called a bra,

505
00:18:55,320 --> 00:18:56,360
this one is called a ket,

506
00:18:56,440 --> 00:18:57,720
and the whole thing makes a braket,

507
00:18:59,160 --> 00:19:00,380
which is British law.

508
00:19:00,400 --> 00:19:01,020
British for bracket.

509
00:19:07,980 --> 00:19:08,660
Okay?

510
00:19:09,160 --> 00:19:11,400
The average value of sigma M,

511
00:19:13,439 --> 00:19:15,789
knowing that it was originally

512
00:19:15,789 --> 00:19:18,140
oriented along the N direction

513
00:19:20,300 --> 00:19:22,740
and measured along the M direction,

514
00:19:24,220 --> 00:19:26,860
is the cosine of the angle between N and M,

515
00:19:26,980 --> 00:19:29,000
which can also be written as

516
00:19:29,000 --> 00:19:30,080
