517
00:19:32,480 --> 00:19:34,780
the ordinary dot product of the vectors,

518
00:19:34,940 --> 00:19:39,200
or just the component of N along M.

519
00:19:39,880 --> 00:19:42,340
The spin was oriented in the N direction,

520
00:19:42,580 --> 00:19:44,260
you measured it along the M direction,

521
00:19:44,480 --> 00:19:47,700
and the answer is plus or minus one,

522
00:19:47,900 --> 00:19:49,320
but on the average,

523
00:19:50,200 --> 00:19:53,340
it's what a classical physicist might have expected

524
00:19:54,220 --> 00:19:56,520
if he measured the component of a spin

525
00:19:56,520 --> 00:19:57,750
which is oriented in one

526
00:19:57,750 --> 00:19:58,980
direction along some other direction.

527
00:19:59,000 --> 00:20:03,140
This is exactly the component of M along N.

528
00:20:04,160 --> 00:20:04,820
Alright,

529
00:20:04,820 --> 00:20:05,040
so,

530
00:20:06,220 --> 00:20:07,980
if you do the experiment many,

531
00:20:07,980 --> 00:20:08,520
many times

532
00:20:08,520 --> 00:20:09,480
and collect averages,

533
00:20:10,419 --> 00:20:11,500
it seems,

534
00:20:11,500 --> 00:20:11,960
in fact,

535
00:20:11,960 --> 00:20:15,660
that the average quantities do behave like vectors,

536
00:20:15,800 --> 00:20:17,320
or like three vectors.

537
00:20:17,840 --> 00:20:20,740
But the individual experiments are very resistant

538
00:20:20,740 --> 00:20:23,620
to giving any answer other than plus or minus one.

539
00:20:25,200 --> 00:20:25,860
Okay,

540
00:20:25,860 --> 00:20:26,800
so this now...

541
00:20:28,979 --> 00:20:31,680
The apparatus doesn't know how to give any answer

542
00:20:31,680 --> 00:20:33,040
other than plus or minus one.

543
00:20:33,160 --> 00:20:34,900
It doesn't know how to give any.

544
00:20:36,000 --> 00:20:38,760
You might try to build another apparatus that does better,

545
00:20:38,880 --> 00:20:39,780
but it won't do better.

546
00:20:41,580 --> 00:20:44,220
Make sure I understand the setup here.

547
00:20:44,320 --> 00:20:47,460
The setup is that you prepare the...

548
00:20:48,500 --> 00:20:49,960
The spin along the N axis.

549
00:20:51,400 --> 00:20:53,540
And then you measure it along the M axis.

550
00:20:54,260 --> 00:20:54,700
Right.

551
00:20:55,220 --> 00:20:56,660
And you get a random answer,

552
00:20:57,100 --> 00:20:58,340
but random biased.

553
00:20:59,300 --> 00:21:00,860
Biased in such a way that the...

554
00:21:01,440 --> 00:21:03,180
that the average is N dot M.

555
00:21:03,420 --> 00:21:03,780
That,

556
00:21:03,780 --> 00:21:04,300
for example,

557
00:21:04,300 --> 00:21:04,820
would mean

