00:52:01,560 --> 00:52:06,720
Is there any description that the orthogonal vectors

1421
00:52:06,720 --> 00:52:09,040
have to be perpendicular to each other?

1422
00:52:09,540 --> 00:52:10,820
That's what orthogonal means.

1423
00:52:11,360 --> 00:52:11,960
Well,

1424
00:52:11,960 --> 00:52:13,580
suppose you have a cube,

1425
00:52:13,600 --> 00:52:16,320
and then you sort of tilt it like a parallelogram.

1426
00:52:16,520 --> 00:52:18,060
It's still three dimensional,

1427
00:52:18,340 --> 00:52:20,500
but the coordinate systems are not perpendicular.

1428
00:52:20,880 --> 00:52:21,480
One of them is not.

1429
00:52:21,700 --> 00:52:25,400
Perpendicular and orthogonal are synonymous terms.

1430
00:52:25,720 --> 00:52:26,400
It is the long term,

1431
00:52:26,400 --> 00:52:27,440
but it has a wide angle.

1432
00:52:27,620 --> 00:52:27,960
You know what I'm saying?

1433
00:52:29,000 --> 00:52:30,820
Perpendicular and orthogonal both mean right angle.

1434
00:52:34,160 --> 00:52:35,400
You're confused by something,

1435
00:52:35,520 --> 00:52:36,460
and I don't know what it is.

1436
00:52:36,640 --> 00:52:37,660
I'm confused by the one.

1437
00:52:40,700 --> 00:52:41,080
Yeah,

1438
00:52:41,080 --> 00:52:41,460
yeah,

1439
00:52:41,460 --> 00:52:42,760
I know you are.

1440
00:52:44,360 --> 00:52:44,920
But...

1441
00:52:48,780 --> 00:52:49,340
Perpendicular,

1442
00:52:49,340 --> 00:52:49,900
orthogonal,

1443
00:52:49,900 --> 00:52:51,420
right angles,

1444
00:52:51,740 --> 00:52:53,260
they mean all the same things.

1445
00:52:53,860 --> 00:52:56,220
I think you think about linearly independent

1446
00:52:56,220 --> 00:52:57,660
versus being fully orthogonal.

1447
00:52:58,060 --> 00:53:00,220
But if you have a set of linearly independent vectors,

1448
00:53:00,320 --> 00:53:02,100
you can extract an orthogonal set out of them.

1449
00:53:02,420 --> 00:53:03,060
This is true.

1450
00:53:03,960 --> 00:53:05,360
He's not confused.

1451
00:53:07,020 --> 00:53:07,840
This is right.

1452
00:53:09,280 --> 00:53:11,800
Linearly independent is different than orthogonal.

1453
00:53:11,800 --> 00:53:14,280
Orthogonal is linearly independent,

1454
00:53:14,660 --> 00:53:17,500
but linearly independent is less strong than orthogonal.

1455
00:53:18,300 --> 00:53:20,100
These two vectors like that,

1456
00:53:20,280 --> 00:53:21,420
they're linearly independent,

1457
00:53:21,800 --> 00:53:22,680
but they're not orthogonal.

1458
00:53:22,980 --> 00:53:23,720
Those are orthogonal.

1459
00:53:25,800 --> 00:53:26,400
Okay,

1460
00:53:26,400 --> 00:53:27,000
let's...

1461
00:53:27,000 --> 00:53:27,840
We'll come back.

1462
00:53:29,840 --> 00:53:30,600
All right.

1463
00:53:30,620 --> 00:53:32,060
The states of a quantum system,

1464
00:53:32,300 --> 00:53:33,520
this is a postulate,

1465
00:53:34,340 --> 00:53:35,780
form a vector space,

1466
00:53:36,720 --> 00:53:38,440
form a complex vector space.

1467
00:53:38,860 --> 00:53:39,840
In fact,

1468
00:53:39,840 --> 00:53:41,660
the space of the simple system,

1469
00:53:41,660 --> 00:53:42,580
we've been discussing,

1470
00:53:42,740 --> 00:53:44,940
form a two-dimensional vector space.

1471
00:53:48,080 --> 00:53:49,460
Let's write down some vectors.

1472
00:53:49,560 --> 00:53:50,320
We know some states.

1473
00:53:50,880 --> 00:53:51,660
We know,

1474
00:53:51,660 --> 00:53:52,100
for example,

1475
00:53:52,100 --> 00:53:53,120
that there is a state

1476
00:53:53,120 --> 00:53:55,600
that can be prepared in which

1477
00:53:55,600 --> 00:53:59,480
the spin is pointing upward along the z-axis.

1478
00:54:01,600 --> 00:54:04,260
We characterize the state by the experiment

1479
00:54:04,260 --> 00:54:06,760
that we did to get it in that state.

1480
00:54:09,040 --> 00:54:10,160
That experiment...

1481
00:54:12,100 --> 00:54:14,820
had the apparatus vertically upward,

1482
00:54:15,620 --> 00:54:17,940
and it created a state of the system

1483
00:54:18,380 --> 00:54:20,340
which either could have been down or up,

1484
00:54:20,420 --> 00:54:21,940
but let's say it's up.

1485
00:54:23,260 --> 00:54:25,520
We can label that state in a number of ways.

1486
00:54:25,620 --> 00:54:26,360
We can call it up.

1487
00:54:26,420 --> 00:54:27,220
We can call it down.

1488
00:54:27,380 --> 00:54:28,060
We can call it plus.

1489
00:54:28,280 --> 00:54:28,880
We can call it...

1490
00:54:28,880 --> 00:54:29,360
Well,

1491
00:54:29,360 --> 00:54:32,100
up and down are the same as plus and minus.

1492
00:54:32,200 --> 00:54:34,860
We could draw them with little arrows up and down.

1493
00:54:35,180 --> 00:54:36,720
What other ways could we...

1494
00:54:36,720 --> 00:54:40,320
We could write it as sigma z equals plus one,

1495
00:54:40,320 --> 00:54:42,400
and sigma z equals minus one.

1496
00:54:42,520 --> 00:54:43,520
They all mean the same thing.

1497
00:54:44,380 --> 00:54:44,900
Up,

1498
00:54:44,900 --> 00:54:45,300
down,

1499
00:54:45,300 --> 00:54:47,100
plus,

1500
00:54:47,100 --> 00:54:47,580
minus,

1501
00:54:47,780 --> 00:54:49,480
sigma z equals plus one,

1502
00:54:49,540 --> 00:54:50,740
sigma z equals minus one,

1503
00:54:50,780 --> 00:54:51,920
all the same thing.

1504
00:54:52,480 --> 00:54:53,180
All right?

1505
00:54:53,300 --> 00:54:55,620
So there are two states that we know about

1506
00:54:55,620 --> 00:54:59,120
that we can access by putting the...

1507
00:54:59,120 --> 00:55:02,820
or we can prepare by turning our apparatus upward

1508
00:55:02,820 --> 00:55:04,380
along the z-axis.

1509
00:55:05,020 --> 00:55:06,100
Let's give them names.

1510
00:55:06,960 --> 00:55:09,140
These states are vectors in a vector space

1511
00:55:09,140 --> 00:55:10,300
according to hypotheses.

1512
00:55:10,320 --> 00:55:13,200
And they can be called,

1513
00:55:13,200 --> 00:55:13,860
let's say,

1514
00:55:13,860 --> 00:55:14,920
up and down.

1515
00:55:22,120 --> 00:55:23,770
If it is true that

1516
00:55:23,770 --> 00:55:25,420
the vector space is as simple

1517
00:55:25,420 --> 00:55:27,480
as just a two-dimensional vector space,

1518
00:55:28,380 --> 00:55:31,260
then that means that any vector in that space

1519
00:55:31,260 --> 00:55:34,480
can be written as some linear combination

1520
00:55:34,480 --> 00:55:35,960
of up and down.

1521
00:55:36,840 --> 00:55:37,900
In other words,

1522
00:55:37,900 --> 00:55:38,600
every vector

1523
00:55:38,840 --> 00:55:40,300
in a two-dimensional space

1524
00:55:40,320 --> 00:55:44,740
can be written in terms of two basis vectors,

1525
00:55:45,000 --> 00:55:45,800
up and down.

1526
00:55:47,140 --> 00:55:49,700
So that's enough to write any state whatever.

1527
00:55:50,340 --> 00:55:50,980
Up,

1528
00:55:50,980 --> 00:55:51,500
down.

1529
00:55:53,620 --> 00:55:54,420
All right,

1530
00:55:54,420 --> 00:55:54,800
what about,

1531
00:55:54,800 --> 00:55:55,180
though,

1532
00:55:55,200 --> 00:55:57,060
the state which is made

1533
00:55:57,060 --> 00:56:01,620
by tilting our apparatus along the x-axis?

1534
00:56:03,360 --> 00:56:04,780
We get something different.

1535
00:56:04,960 --> 00:56:06,000
It's not the same thing.

1536
00:56:06,220 --> 00:56:07,440
It's not up,

1537
00:56:07,440 --> 00:56:10,240
because up means up along the z-axis.

1538
00:56:11,060 --> 00:56:12,080
It's not down,

1539
00:56:12,140 --> 00:56:14,060
because down means down along the z-axis.

1540
00:56:14,720 --> 00:56:16,240
And we know they're different

1541
00:56:16,240 --> 00:56:18,480
because we know the results of experiments

1542
00:56:18,960 --> 00:56:20,840
on these two different kinds of states

1543
00:56:20,840 --> 00:56:21,960
will in general be different.

1544
00:56:24,100 --> 00:56:24,620
So,

1545
00:56:24,620 --> 00:56:26,540
we can call those states...

1546
00:56:26,540 --> 00:56:28,420
I tend to call them left and right.

1547
00:56:29,100 --> 00:56:30,700
There's up and down.

1548
00:56:30,800 --> 00:56:32,320
There's right and left.

1549
00:56:33,700 --> 00:56:35,000
Those are two other states.

1550
00:56:35,240 --> 00:56:37,040
We could draw them this way if we liked.

1551
00:56:37,940 --> 00:56:41,400
They also correspond to sigma x equals one

1552
00:56:41,400 --> 00:56:43,720
and sigma x equals minus one.

1553
00:56:45,240 --> 00:56:47,420
And we could label them if we liked.

1554
00:56:48,700 --> 00:56:52,260
Let's label them right and left.

1555
00:56:54,280 --> 00:56:54,960
Finally,

1556
00:56:54,960 --> 00:56:57,520
we know that if we were to turn our apparatus

1557
00:56:57,520 --> 00:57:03,260
so that the apparatus was pointing along the y-axis,

1558
00:57:03,620 --> 00:57:06,440
we could access two more states.

1559
00:57:06,440 --> 00:57:09,820
I think we call those in and out,

1560
00:57:09,860 --> 00:57:12,120
into the blackboard and out of the blackboard.

1561
00:57:12,460 --> 00:57:13,300
And so,

1562
00:57:13,300 --> 00:57:15,420
there's in and out.

1563
00:57:18,700 --> 00:57:20,740
Into the blackboard and out of the blackboard.

1564
00:57:20,900 --> 00:57:22,910
And they correspond to sigma

1565
00:57:22,910 --> 00:57:24,920
y equals plus or minus one.

1566
00:57:26,040 --> 00:57:30,440
We could label them in and out.

1567
00:57:32,860 --> 00:57:36,340
All of the logic that I've described to you

1568
00:57:36,340 --> 00:57:38,260
and all of the experimental results,

1569
00:57:39,880 --> 00:57:41,120
as we will see,

1570
00:57:41,120 --> 00:57:42,560
we will not see it immediately,

1571
00:57:42,900 --> 00:57:45,460
it took some time to understand all of this,

1572
00:57:46,140 --> 00:57:50,420
it is all summarized by a few statements,

1573
00:57:51,140 --> 00:57:53,190
but the first of which is

1574
00:57:53,190 --> 00:57:55,240
that the space of all states

1575
00:57:55,240 --> 00:57:57,340
of that simple system is two-dimensional,

1576
00:57:58,320 --> 00:58:00,680
has only two independent states,

1577
00:58:00,840 --> 00:58:05,680
which means that these other things can be written

1578
00:58:05,680 --> 00:58:06,940
in terms of up and down.

1579
00:58:08,100 --> 00:58:08,660
Okay,

1580
00:58:08,660 --> 00:58:12,580
so let's go to general linear combinations

1581
00:58:12,580 --> 00:58:14,860
of up and down and ask what they mean.

1582
00:58:15,800 --> 00:58:17,680
Let's take a vector,

1583
00:58:17,680 --> 00:58:20,120
I guess we can call it A,

1584
00:58:21,200 --> 00:58:24,180
which is of the form a coefficient,

1585
00:58:24,420 --> 00:58:28,720
a complex coefficient alpha one times up,

1586
00:58:29,280 --> 00:58:30,700
plus another complex,

1587
00:58:30,700 --> 00:58:31,640
another,

1588
00:58:31,640 --> 00:58:33,800
I suppose we should call this alpha up.

1589
00:58:33,860 --> 00:58:34,660
Alpha up.

1590
00:58:35,680 --> 00:58:37,700
Alpha down times down.

1591
00:58:38,360 --> 00:58:40,700
The alphas are complex numbers.

1592
00:58:41,940 --> 00:58:43,580
In complex vector spaces,

1593
00:58:43,580 --> 00:58:44,560
you multiply,

1594
00:58:44,840 --> 00:58:45,800
they could be real numbers,

1595
00:58:46,580 --> 00:58:47,380
but in general,

1596
00:58:47,380 --> 00:58:48,860
they will be complex numbers.

1597
00:58:52,260 --> 00:58:54,400
Let us suppose we knew what that meant,

1598
00:58:54,600 --> 00:58:56,360
what kind of state this was,

1599
00:58:56,360 --> 00:58:57,480
where it came from.

1600
00:58:58,160 --> 00:58:59,280
It's a new beast,

1601
00:58:59,280 --> 00:59:00,320
it's not up,

1602
00:59:00,320 --> 00:59:01,200
it's not down,

1603
00:59:01,340 --> 00:59:02,440
somewhere in between.

1604
00:59:05,020 --> 00:59:06,060
Next postulate.

1605
00:59:06,220 --> 00:59:08,210
The next postulate is that if

1606
00:59:08,210 --> 00:59:10,200
we were to measure up and down,

1607
00:59:10,260 --> 00:59:12,600
if somebody prepared us an electron

1608
00:59:12,600 --> 00:59:14,940
or a spin in this state

1609
00:59:14,940 --> 00:59:16,260
and we measured up and down,

1610
00:59:16,520 --> 00:59:19,300
we would find probabilities for up and down,

1611
00:59:19,500 --> 00:59:21,940
and those probabilities would be

1612
00:59:22,960 --> 00:59:24,240
probability for up

1613
00:59:29,740 --> 00:59:32,420
is the square of the magnitude of the force.

1614
00:59:32,420 --> 00:59:33,440
So if we were to measure up and down,

1615
00:59:33,440 --> 00:59:34,820
we would have the magnitude of this coefficient

1616
00:59:34,820 --> 00:59:37,320
and probability for down

1617
00:59:38,020 --> 00:59:40,120
is equal to alpha star down,

1618
00:59:40,120 --> 00:59:41,120
alpha down.

1619
00:59:41,940 --> 00:59:43,160
In other words,

1620
00:59:43,160 --> 00:59:45,680
it's basically the square of the coefficient

1621
00:59:45,680 --> 00:59:47,440
or the square of the component

1622
00:59:49,420 --> 00:59:53,360
of A in the directions up and down.

1623
00:59:53,740 --> 00:59:54,940
These alphas,

1624
00:59:54,940 --> 00:59:56,560
they're essentially the components

1625
00:59:56,560 --> 00:59:59,820
of a general vector along the two axes,

1626
00:59:59,820 --> 01:00:01,540
up and down.

1627
01:00:06,160 --> 01:00:08,140
There's something that I failed to tell you.

1628
01:00:08,260 --> 01:00:09,360
It's also a postulate.

1629
01:00:09,460 --> 01:00:09,760
There are many,

1630
01:00:09,760 --> 01:00:10,440
many postulates,

1631
01:00:10,520 --> 01:00:12,600
but you'll see they fit together in a neat package.

1632
01:00:13,420 --> 01:00:17,080
There are probably fewer postulates than I'm saying.

1633
01:00:18,720 --> 01:00:21,680
I'll bet we can reduce it down to four postulates,

1634
01:00:22,740 --> 01:00:23,700
four axioms.

1635
01:00:24,160 --> 01:00:26,960
But rather than try to axiomatize it,

1636
01:00:27,080 --> 01:00:27,780
we'll just...

1637
01:00:30,280 --> 01:00:32,280
do it a little more informally.

1638
01:00:33,380 --> 01:00:35,400
What's the relation between up and down?

1639
01:00:38,620 --> 01:00:41,660
Are they the negative of each other?

1640
01:00:42,800 --> 01:00:43,400
No,

1641
01:00:43,400 --> 01:00:43,980
they're orthogonal.

1642
01:00:44,780 --> 01:00:45,380
Now,

1643
01:00:45,380 --> 01:00:45,980
that's a postulate.

1644
01:00:46,380 --> 01:00:48,960
The basic postulate is when things

1645
01:00:49,720 --> 01:00:51,260
are measurably different.

1646
01:00:52,080 --> 01:00:55,780
When two states are such that you can cleanly

1647
01:00:55,780 --> 01:00:58,100
tell the difference between them by an experiment,

1648
01:00:58,600 --> 01:00:59,700
they are orthogonal.

1649
01:01:01,620 --> 01:01:04,120
Orthogonality literally means they are

1650
01:01:05,920 --> 01:01:08,320
sufficiently different that you can,

1651
01:01:08,460 --> 01:01:09,940
with a single experiment,

1652
01:01:10,120 --> 01:01:12,000
or maybe a few experiments,

1653
01:01:12,080 --> 01:01:13,940
tell the difference between them uniquely.

1654
01:01:15,320 --> 01:01:16,410
I'll tell you what it

1655
01:01:16,410 --> 01:01:17,500
corresponds to in terms of sets.

1656
01:01:21,900 --> 01:01:23,980
You might say that two sets are orthogonal

1657
01:01:23,980 --> 01:01:25,940
if they don't share any elements.

1658
01:01:26,140 --> 01:01:27,440
This is not a standard terminology.

1659
01:01:28,060 --> 01:01:29,320
But you might say it anyway.

1660
01:01:29,320 --> 01:01:31,280
They're orthogonal if they don't share any elements.

1661
01:01:32,600 --> 01:01:34,440
That means they're distinctly different.

1662
01:01:34,960 --> 01:01:36,920
There's no chance that an experiment

1663
01:01:36,920 --> 01:01:38,220
will confuse the two of them.

1664
01:01:38,940 --> 01:01:40,300
An experiment will...

1665
01:01:40,300 --> 01:01:43,200
a nice experiment to distinguish them

1666
01:01:43,200 --> 01:01:45,000
will not lead to any ambiguity.

1667
01:01:45,560 --> 01:01:47,300
The same is true of up and down.

1668
01:01:47,400 --> 01:01:48,860
Up is distinctly different than down.

1669
01:01:48,940 --> 01:01:49,580
If you measure up,

1670
01:01:49,580 --> 01:01:51,060
you'll measure up again and again and again.

1671
01:01:51,800 --> 01:01:54,660
And the version of that in quantum mechanics,

1672
01:01:56,120 --> 01:01:59,140
or the implication of that in quantum mechanics,

1673
01:01:59,140 --> 01:02:00,740
for the vectors,

1674
01:02:01,020 --> 01:02:03,660
is that things that correspond to physically

1675
01:02:04,480 --> 01:02:06,800
unambiguous different situations

1676
01:02:06,800 --> 01:02:08,500
are orthogonal to each other.

1677
01:02:08,760 --> 01:02:11,900
So up and down are orthogonal to each other.

1678
01:02:13,940 --> 01:02:16,540
What if we have a combination of up and down

1679
01:02:16,540 --> 01:02:17,600
with some coefficients?

1680
01:02:18,400 --> 01:02:20,540
Then there's a probability to be up

1681
01:02:20,540 --> 01:02:22,100
and a probability to be down.

1682
01:02:22,360 --> 01:02:25,180
And the probabilities are given by

1683
01:02:26,120 --> 01:02:27,140
alpha star alpha,

1684
01:02:29,140 --> 01:02:31,180
and alpha star alpha down.

1685
01:02:32,420 --> 01:02:32,980
Again,

1686
01:02:32,980 --> 01:02:34,000
that's a postulate,

1687
01:02:34,040 --> 01:02:36,260
but we'll see in a moment what that corresponds to.

1688
01:02:39,060 --> 01:02:39,620
Well,

1689
01:02:39,620 --> 01:02:41,000
what's the relation between

1690
01:02:41,000 --> 01:02:43,220
the probability for up and the probability for down?

1691
01:02:43,540 --> 01:02:45,600
The answer is that if we add them,

1692
01:02:45,720 --> 01:02:46,420
we get one.

1693
01:02:47,820 --> 01:02:48,780
And therefore,

1694
01:02:49,420 --> 01:02:51,920
alpha star alpha plus beta star beta

1695
01:02:51,920 --> 01:02:53,260
is equal to one.

1696
01:02:54,760 --> 01:02:56,780
Any reasonable state of the system

1697
